Package: pulse-sec
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, bash, jq, curl, iproute2, systemd
Recommends: kdialog
Description: Host security pulse-check, CLI + collector
 Composite risk score from fourteen local host probes (firewall, kernel
 age, listening ports, LUKS, SSH, secure boot, suid drift and others)
 cross-referenced against CVE feeds.
 .
 Provides the pulse CLI and pulse-collector daemon. Pulse is Arch-first;
 on Debian and Ubuntu the package-inventory probe is a no-op until a
 dpkg backend lands in v1.x.

Package: pulse-plasmoid
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, pulse-sec, plasma-workspace
Description: KDE Plasma 6 widget for pulse
 Renders the composite score, probe rows and CVE list in the panel.
 Reads JSON state written by pulse-collector.
